Preheat your #oven{} (for the tortillas) to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Chop the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Juice half the @lime{1} and cut the rest into thick wedges.

> TIP: If you want to avoid turning on your oven you can dry-fry your tortillas in a pan instead!

== Pickled Onion ==

In a #bowl{}, mix the lime juice with ¼ tsp @salt{1/4%tsp} and ¼ tsp @sugar{1/4%tsp}.

Add half the onion.

Give it a good stir then set aside.

== Mince and Beans ==

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat (without oil).

Once hot, add the @turkey mince{250%grams} and fry until browned, ~{6-8%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once browned, add the remaining onion and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @tomato paste{2%sachet} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add 100ml @water{100%ml} to the pan along with the @chicken stock{1%sachet} and stir to dissolve.

Stir in the black beans and gently crush with the back of a #fork{}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir through a knob of @butter{knob} and the @chipotle paste{1%sachet}.

== Tomatoes ==

Meanwhile, add the tomatoes to a bowl.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with salt and pepper and mix well to combine.

When the mince is nearly ready, pop the @tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to the mince if you feel it's become too dry.

== To Serve ==

Divide the warmed tortillas between #plates{} and spoon over the mince and black bean mixture.

Top with the @salad leaves{40%grams} then spoon over the tomatoes.

Finish with the pickled onion and drizzle of @mayo{2%sachet}.

Serve with lime wedges alongside.